# Calendar app — backup manifest.
#
# This app's persistent data does NOT live inside the repo. It lives in
# ~/.claude/data/calendar/ (see src/lib/data-paths.ts) so it survives builds and
# deployments. The backup script only resolves manifest paths relative to the app
# repo dir (no $HOME/env expansion), so those files cannot be referenced here.
#
# They are backed up instead by the "External paths outside the app roots"
# section of ~/bin/backup-app-data.sh (dbckz/backup-scripts), which already
# covers time-tracking.json. That section needs these two lines added so the
# primary SQLite store and the integration credentials are captured too:
#
#   backup_sqlite "$HOME/.claude/data/calendar/calendar.db"        "calendar_calendar.db"
#   backup_file   "$HOME/.claude/data/calendar/integrations.json"  "calendar_integrations.json"
#
# (calendar.db must use backup_sqlite — the sqlite3 .backup command it runs takes
# a WAL-consistent snapshot. workflow-config.json is regenerable from defaults, so
# it is optional.)
#
# This manifest is intentionally left with no active entries: there is nothing
# in-repo to back up, and its presence suppresses the script's "unregistered
# data" audit warning for this app.
